result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant John Lee Tarris was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.
  • Unlawful Phone Use-Threaten w/ Obscenity, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.012(1)(b).
  • Computer Message-Threaten/Obscenity, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.0125(2)(c).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Mental Health assessment and any other assessment and counseling as required and follow through and complete all required treatment.

timeConds.notes: Pursuant to Stipulation and Order Amending Judgment of Conviction dated 04/06/2016, defendant may serve sentence in Rusk County in Wisconsin as long as there is no additional cost to Chippewa County.  (The Judgment of Conviction was not filed prior to the Stipulation and Order so it will not be on file as an Amended).
